    "## 🌳 Phase 3: Decision Tree from Scratch (Week 5-6)\n",
    "\n",
    "### What You Need to Learn:\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3.1 How Decision Trees Work\n",
    "\n",
    "**Concept:**\n",
    "A Decision Tree asks yes/no questions to classify data:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Is flaeche_m2 > 1000?\n",
    "├── Yes → Is qualitaet == 'PN'?\n",
    "│   ├── Yes → Predict: 'Gebaeude'\n",
    "│   └── No → Predict: 'Wald'\n",
    "└── No → Is shape_area > 5000?\n",
    "    ├── Yes → Predict: 'Landwirtschaft'\n",
    "    └── No → Predict: 'Strasse'\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Concepts:**\n",
    "- **Root node:** First split (top of tree)\n",
    "- **Internal nodes:** Decision points\n",
    "- **Leaf nodes:** Final predictions\n",
    "- **Depth:** How many levels deep\n",
    "- **Pruning:** Stop tree from overfitting\n",
    "\n",
    "**Resources:**\n",
    "- 📹 [Decision Tree Algorithm (StatQuest)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7VeUPuFGUHA) ⭐ BEST EXPLANATION\n",
    "- 📹 [Decision Trees Explained](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eM4uJ6XGnSM)\n",
    "- 📖 [Decision Trees - A Simple Explanation](https://victorzhou.com/blog/decision-trees/)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3.2 Impurity Measures (Gini & Entropy)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:** Decide which feature to split on\n",
    "\n",
    "**Gini Impurity:**\n",
    "```python\n",
    "def gini_impurity(y):\n",
    "    # y = array of labels, e.g., [0, 0, 1, 2, 1, 0]\n",
    "    n = len(y)\n",
    "    _, counts = np.unique(y, return_counts=True)\n",
    "    probs = counts / n\n",
    "    gini = 1 - np.sum(probs ** 2)\n",
    "    return gini\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Entropy:**\n",
    "```python\n",
    "def entropy(y):\n",
    "    n = len(y)\n",
    "    _, counts = np.unique(y, return_counts=True)\n",
    "    probs = counts / n\n",
    "    entropy = -np.sum(probs * np.log2(probs))\n",
    "    return entropy\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Information Gain:**\n",
    "```python\n",
    "def information_gain(y, y_left, y_right):\n",
    "    n = len(y)\n",
    "    n_left, n_right = len(y_left), len(y_right)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    gain = entropy(y) - (\n",
    "        (n_left / n) * entropy(y_left) + \n",
    "        (n_right / n) * entropy(y_right)\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return gain\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Resources:**\n",
    "- 📹 [Gini Impurity (StatQuest)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9h3z5vTqPJA)\n",
    "- 📹 [Entropy & Information Gain](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1ukSK1WraAo)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3.3 Building the Decision Tree Algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "**Step-by-Step:**\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Start with all data** at root node\n",
    "2. **For each feature**, find best split:\n",
    "   - Try all threshold values\n",
    "   - Calculate information gain\n",
    "   - Keep best split\n",
    "3. **Choose feature** with highest information gain\n",
    "4. **Split data** into left and right branches\n",
    "5. **Repeat recursively** for each branch\n",
    "6. **Stop when:**\n",
    "   - Max depth reached\n",
    "   - All samples same class\n",
    "   - No samples left\n",
    "\n",
    "**Class Structure:**\n",
    "```python\n",
    "class DecisionTreeClassifier:\n",
    "    def __init__(self, max_depth=5, min_samples_split=2):\n",
    "        self.max_depth = max_depth\n",
    "        self.min_samples_split = min_samples_split\n",
    "        self.tree = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def fit(self, X, y):\n",
    "        # Build the tree recursively\n",
    "        self.tree = self._build_tree(X, y, depth=0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _build_tree(self, X, y, depth):\n",
    "        # 1. Check stopping criteria\n",
    "        # 2. Find best split\n",
    "        # 3. Create node\n",
    "        # 4. Recursively build left and right\n",
    "        pass\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _find_best_split(self, X, y):\n",
    "        # Try all features and thresholds\n",
    "        # Return best feature, threshold, and gain\n",
    "        pass\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def predict(self, X):\n",
    "        # Traverse tree for each sample\n",
    "        return np.array([self._traverse_tree(x, self.tree) for x in X])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _traverse_tree(self, x, node):\n",
    "        # If leaf node, return prediction\n",
    "        # Otherwise, go left or right based on feature value\n",
    "        pass\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Resources:**\n",
    "- 📖 [Build Decision Tree from Scratch](https://victorzhou.com/blog/decision-trees/)\n",
    "- 💻 [Example Implementation](https://github.com/python-engineer/MLfromScratch/blob/master/decision_tree.py)\n",
    "\n",
