    "\n",
    "## 📈 Phase 4: Model Evaluation (Week 7-8)\n",
    "\n",
    "### What You Need to Learn:\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 4.1 Classification Metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "**Accuracy:**\n",
    "```python\n",
    "accuracy = correct_predictions / total_predictions\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Precision, Recall, F1:**\n",
    "```python\n",
    "precision = true_positives / (true_positives + false_positives)\n",
    "recall = true_positives / (true_positives + false_negatives)\n",
    "f1 = 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Confusion Matrix:**\n",
    "```\n",
    "              Predicted\n",
    "              Yes    No\n",
    "Actual Yes    TP     FN\n",
    "       No     FP     TN\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Resources:**\n",
    "- 📹 [Classification Metrics (StatQuest)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kdsp6dkqAe0)\n",
    "- 📖 [Understanding Classification Metrics](https://towardsdatascience.com/accuracy-precision-recall-or-f1-331fb37c5cb9)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 4.2 Cross-Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why:** Better estimate of model performance\n",
    "\n",
    "**K-Fold Cross-Validation:**\n",
    "1. Split data into K folds (e.g., K=5)\n",
    "2. Train on K-1 folds, test on 1 fold\n",
    "3. Repeat K times (each fold used as test once)\n",
    "4. Average performance across all K runs\n",
    "\n",
    "**Resources:**\n",
    "- 📹 [Cross-Validation (StatQuest)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fSytzGwwBVw)\n",
    "\n",
